rbind or cbind mass_dataset

Xiaotao Shen (https://www.shenxt.info/)

Created on 2021-12-04 and updated on 2022-03-11

Source: vignettes/cbind_rbind_mass_dataset.Rmd
cbind_rbind_mass_dataset.Rmd

If you have two mass_dataset, you can use cbind or rbind to merge them as one mass_dataset.

cbind()

cbind() means that two mass_dataset have same variabels and totally different samples.

library(massdataset)
library(tidyverse)

data("expression_data")
data("sample_info")
data("sample_info_note")
data("variable_info")
data("variable_info_note")

object =
  create_mass_dataset(
    expression_data = expression_data,
    sample_info = sample_info,
    variable_info = variable_info,
    sample_info_note = sample_info_note,
    variable_info_note = variable_info_note
  )
  
object

rbind()

rbind() means that two mass_dataset have same samples and totally different variables

object1 = 
  object[1:10,]

object2 = 
  object[11:15,]

rownames(object1)
#>  [1] "M136T55_2_POS" "M79T35_POS"    "M307T548_POS"  "M183T224_POS" 
#>  [5] "M349T47_POS"   "M182T828_POS"  "M299T359_POS"  "M348T844_POS"

rownames(object2)
